@5DN1L, Yup I like the new constraints and test cases. However, it still bugs me that there are only 3 possible output strings. In a clash, someone could just type one line: print("yes") and get a 38% score, which can possibly win if you play against bots with 0% score responses. Unfortunately, I don't think that's possible to prevent for this specific puzzle.
@j3r3m, thanks for fixing your constraints and test cases; they're more coordinated now.
Very small and minor fix in the constraints: 1 ≤ [[dist]] <= 20 to 1 ≤ [[dist]] ≤ 20
